  "prompt": "How can I work for Amazon?",
  "response": "To work for Amazon, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the Amazon Jobs website\n- Go to amazon.jobs/careers\n- Browse available positions\n\n2. Search and apply for positions\n- Use filters for location, job type, and department\n- Create an online profile\n- Upload your resume\n- Complete the online application\n\n3. Types of job opportunities\n- Corporate roles (tech, marketing, finance)\n- Warehouse and fulfillment center positions\n- Customer service\n- Cloud computing (AWS)\n- Software development\n- Delivery driver (Amazon Flex)\n- Seasonal positions\n\n4. Minimum requirements\n- Typically 18+ years old\n- High school diploma or equivalent\n- Valid ID\n- Ability to pass background check\n- Physical stamina for warehouse/delivery jobs\n\n5. Prepare for the application process\n- Tailor your resume to the specific role\n- Highlight relevant skills and experience\n- Be ready for potential online assessments\n- Prepare for interviews (in-person or virtual)\n\n6. Consider alternative entry points\n- Internships\n- Entry-level positions\n- Temporary or contract work\n\nTips: Check Amazon's careers website regularly, network with current employees, and be persistent in your job search.",
